The Herald HERENTALS team manager Oliver Chirenga said he went through difficult time trying to clear his name of any wrongdoing in the match fixing allegations which they were acquitted of on Friday. Chirenga who has been with the club since it formative years playing as a social soccer until it was promoted in the top flight some two season ago said it was hard for him and the rest of the team. “I am very happy that my name has been cleared and we will be back in the top flight. It was very hard times for us and we are now happy that justice was eventually meet out. “Football is part of my life and I was wondering what it was going to be if the life ban was to be implemented,” said Chirenga. 